y http www documents dgs ca gov osp GovernorsBudget03 pdf bth pdf Department of Financial Institutions Budget 2002 2003 Governor s Budget mission asp DFI Mission Vision and Values about dfi photo asp DFI Photo Gallery exec profiles asp Executive Profiles institutions supervised asp Institutions Supervised mission asp Mission Statement office locations asp Office Locations orgchart pdf Organization Chart Department of Financial Institutions My CA This Site Executive Profiles DONALD R MEYER Commissioner of Financial Institutions Donald R Meyer was appointed Commissioner of Financial Institutions of the State of California on April 4 2000 He holds a B A in Political Science from UC Berkeley a J D from Boalt Hall School of Law at UC Berkeley and did graduate work at Harvard University Graduate School of Business Administration Mr Meyer served in the Peace Corps in Seoul Korea from 1968 to 1970 He was admitted to the California State Bar in January 1972 He was an attorney at Graham James in San Francisco from 1971 to 1976 Vice President General Counsel and Assistant Corporate Secretary of California First Bank from 1976 to 1978 Senior Vice President General Counsel and Assistant Corporate Secretary of Union Bank from 1978 to 1996 Executive Vice President General Counsel and Corporate Secretary of UnionBanCal Corporation from April 1996 to July 1998 and served as counsel in the San Francisco law firm of McCutchen Doyle Brown Enersen from July 1998 to November 1998 Mr Meyer has been active in the California Bankers Association by serving on its Legal Affairs and Federal Government Relations Committees He received CBA s Almon B McCallum Award for outstanding service to the banking industry in 1989 Mr Meyer has served as the California State Vice President for the American Bankers Association and he was a member of the ABA Government Relations Council for many years Mr Meyer has been a credit union member for more than 30 years Mr Meyer is a member of the World Affairs Council of Northern California Society of California Pioneers and the Sierra Club In addition to serving on the American Asian Cultural Exchange Advisory Board he is past President and current Chairman of the Board of Directors of the Korean American Chamber of Commerce and serves as trustee of the Asian Art Museum Foundation CAROL D CHESBROUGH Chief Deputy Commissioner Carol D Chesbrough was appointed Chief Deputy Commissioner on June 14 2001 by Donald R Meyer Commissioner of Financial Institutions Ms Chesbrough has over 20 years experience in State of California government law and policy positions Trained as an attorney she has held positions as an appellate court attorney deputy attorney general hearing officer and senior counsel Her policy roles include advisor to Former Energy Commissioner Geoffrey Commons and to the Director of Fairs Expositions Recent assignments have been at the Department of Food Agriculture where she served as a Senior Counsel Marketing Division Director and Director of Change Management Ms Chesbrough served as Administrative Advisor and General Counsel to the California Census 2000 Team She received a Superior Accomplishment award Ms Chesbrough received her law degree from the University of the Pacific McGeorge School of Law She was on law review and graduated in the top 10 of her class a member of the Traynor Society now order of the Coif Ms Chesbrough graduated summa cum laude from Humboldt State University graduating second overall Her community activities include being a school board member United Way Chair and a Girl Scout and 4 H leader She has been a member of a credit union for over 20 years ELIZABETH DOOLEY Deputy Commissioner Credit Unions Elizabeth Dooley was appointed to the position of Deputy Commissioner of Credit Unions by Governor Gray Davis on October 31 2000 assuming her duties at the DFI on December 4 2000 Prior to joining the DFI Ms Dooley was Associate Counsel for the California Credit Union League where she advised the League and its affiliated companies as well as credit unions on a variety of issues Before going to the California Credit Union League Ms Dooley was the Treasurer and part owner of Dycorp U S A a retail and mail order business selling performance parts for motorcycles and ATVs Beth began her career as a stockbroker for Dean Witter where she managed over 400 accounts with assets of approximately 5 million Beth has a BA in Economics from Mills College and a Juris Doctorate from Western State University College of Law DAVID L SCOTT Chief State Examiner David L Scott was appointed Chief State Bank Examiner on April 1 1996 He became Chief State Examiner on July 1 1997 when the State Banking Department became the Department of Financial Institutions In his current position he supervises all of the Department s bank examination and bank supervision activities He previously was the Deputy Superintendent of Banks for the State Banking Department s Los Angeles Regional Office Mr Scott joined the California State Banking Department in August 1972 as a junior examiner and has held a variety of positions in the Department Scott earned a bachelor s degree in accounting from California State University at Northridge He also has attended National Commercial Lending School and Pacific Coast Banking School JAMES E BRODIE Deputy Commissioner Division of Examinations Northern California Region James E Brodie was appointed Deputy Superintendent of Banks on March 2 1992 He became Deputy Commissioner on July 1 1997 when the State Banking Department became the Department of Financial Institutions Prior to 1992 he was Assistant Deputy Superintendent of Banks Mr Brodie joined the California State Banking Department now the Department of Financial Institutions as a Bank Examiner I in 1972 and has worked continuously in the San Francisco Regional Office Mr Brodie earned his Bachelor of Arts degree in Economics from the University of California Berkeley He has attended the National Commercial Lending School in Norman Oklahoma as well as numerous technical schools and executive programs CRAIG A CARLSON Deputy Commissioner Division of Examinations San Diego Orange County Region Craig A Carlson was appointed Deputy Commissioner Division of Examinations San Diego Orange County Region on June 18 2001 Mr Carlson joined the California State Banking Department now the Department of Financial Institutions as a Junior Bank Examiner in 1974 and has been an Assistant Deputy Commissioner in the San Diego Office since 1986 He earned his Bachelor of Arts degree in Accounting from San Diego State University and is a graduate of the National Commercial Lending School in Norman Oklahoma JOHN CONNELL Chief Administrative Officer John Connell was appointed Chief Administrative Officer on November 1 2000 by Donald R Meyer Commissioner Mr Connell will be located in the Sacramento Office Mr Connell is a career civil servant and brings 27 years of management experience in state government He is experienced in the areas of personnel contracting procurement accounting budgeting and space management He comes to us from the Department of Food Agriculture CDFA where he was serving as Branch Chief Mr Connell has an extensive background in quality management and is an examiner for the California Council of Quality and Service As a part of the CDFA s executive team Mr Connell served as a member of the Strategic Planning Task Force and was team facilitator for the Information Systems Strategic Plan He has years of public speaking and presentation experience before audiences ranging from the State Legislature to community outreach forums Mr Connell is a graduate of San Jose State with a degree in biology and chemistry MEG SVOBODA Legislative Deputy Commissioner Margaret Meg Svoboda was appointed as Legislative Deputy Commissioner on June 11 2001 Ms Svoboda has extensive legislative experience and her most recent position was as a consultant with the California Assembly Committee on Banking and Finance She formerly served as a fiscal and policy analyst with the Legislative Analyst s Office focusing on business development and regulation Through these positions she had responsibility for analyzing the Department s programs and budget as well as various legislative issues She is an honors graduate of DePauw University and has a master s degree in Public Administration from Columbia University Additionally Ms Svoboda was in the Peace Corps in Africa BRIAN YUEN Deputy Commissioner Division of Examinations Southern California Region Brian Yuen was appointed Deputy Commissioner Division of Examinations Southern California Region effective April 2 2001 Mr Yuen joined the California State Banking Department now the Department of Financial Institutions as a junior bank examiner in 1974 and has been an Assistant Deputy Commissioner in the San Francisco Regional Office since 1991 Mr Yuen is a graduate of San Francisco State University In addition he obtained a Certificate of Banking from the Pacific Coast Banking School at the University of Washington Seattle Documents labeled pdf require Adobe Acrobat Reader A current version of Acrobat is available from http www adobe com products acrobat readstep html Adobe s web site PageTop Back to Top of Page 2003 State of California policies conditions asp Conditions of Use policies privacy asp Privacy Policy Contact the mailto webmaster dfi ca gov Webmaster if you have questions or comments concerning this site 
